// File: Main.java
// Missing import statement!

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ArrayList<String> list = new ArrayList<>();
        list.add("Hello");
    }
}

phase2.explanation:
ArrayList is in the java.util package, but you haven't imported it!

FIX: Add import at the top:
import java.util.ArrayList;

Or use the fully qualified name:
java.util.ArrayList<String> list = new java.util.ArrayList<>();

Remember: Only java.lang is automatically imported. All other packages need explicit import statements.

